title: How many influenza positive viruses will FluNet record for Egypt between 27 November 2017 and 3 December 2017 (epidemiological week 48)?
preds:
Something fishy going on here.  Why did influenza monitoring drop off a cliff in mid-June???  There were more samples submitted in the first week in June than have been submitted since then! If normal monitoring were in place, I would have had a split something like 0.01/0.18/0.37/0.38/0.06
But if current information blackout continues, more like 0.90/0.10/0/0/0 
And I think it is 90% likely the information blackout will continue.

Consensus seems low. There are only sporadic cases in Egypt not like a local outbreak this time last year. However in previous years there are more cases at this time of year. So hedged bets a little.
I estimated the current, near-zero count level with a zero-inflated Poisson model - bootstrapped from the past 10 weeks data.
